  "description": [
    "THE EVENING BULLETIN VOLUME XVII MAYSVILLE KY MONDAY MAY 2 1898 NUMBER 130 S WIPED OFF THE EARTH Was Spanish Fleet Defending Philippine Islands DEWEYS SQUADRON DID IT Americans Sailed Into Manilla and Began the Action NOT A SPANISH SHIP NOW AFLOAT Spanish Official Reports Say They Were All Destroyed AMEEIOAN SHIPS SLIGHTLY HUET The World Is Given a Practical Demon stration of the Fighting Qualities of United States Warships With Their Polyglot Crows Great Rejoic ing In Spain Because the Bpauish Loss Was No Orcatur Madrid April 2 According to offi cial advices received from Manilla there was more than one mule killed at Cavlte and Manilla The Spanish fleet was completely destroyed and the forts silenced The American fleet must have fared remarkably well for even the official reports do not say they lost a ship They do say however that the Ameri cans were damaged The following Is the official dispatch from the governor general of the Phil ippines to the minister of war Lieuten ant General Correa as to the engage ment off Manilla LaBt night April 30 the batteries at the entrance to the fort announced the arrival of the enemys squadron forcing a passage"
  ],
